cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software

title: "GROMACS-Analysis: An integrated Python toolkit for GROMACS simulation preparation and trajectory analysis"
version: 1.2.0
date-released: "2025-05-05"
license: MIT

abstract: >
  GROMACS-Analysis is a Python toolkit that unifies the full GROMACS
  molecular dynamics pipeline — from raw protein structure through
  simulation preparation, equilibration, production run, and
  post-simulation trajectory analysis — into a single coherent,
  documented, and testable codebase. The package provides sim_prep for
  automated preparation of apo, protein-ligand complex, and mixed-solvent
  (MixMD) simulations, and GromacsAnalysis for trajectory analysis
  including RMSD/RMSF, hydrogen bond analysis, SASA, dynamic
  cross-correlation, PCA, free energy landscapes, graph-theoretic network
  analysis, and PDB structure annotation.

